Title: Let's Build & Deploy a MCP Server with C#
Description:
Looking to get started building and testing your own Model Context Protocol (MCP) server? Look no further than the new C# SDK for MCPs. You can build both client and servers with a delightful API that gets you up and running in minutes. Best of all you can build, test, and deploy directly from VS Code.

C# SDK Announcement: https://devblogs.microsoft.com/blog/microsoft-partners-with-anthropic-to-create-official-c-sdk-for-model-context-protocol

Container docs: https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/containers/publish-configuration

00:00 - Intro
02:50 - Create project & install NuGets
04:38 - Boilerplate code and testing MCP server
11:25 - Real MCP server tool functions that call APIs
18:40 - Containerizing and deploying MCP server to docker
23:05 - Wrap-up
